original: Håkansson, Enar A’lf, prakt, läkare, Nässjö, f. 27/4/04 i Turinge, StMms 1, av disp. Oscar Ferdinand H. o. Anna Maria Hallborg. G. m. Margit Persson. Barn: Bengt f. 44’, Hans 46. — Stud :ex. i Västervik 24, med. kand. i Lund 33’, med. lic. i Sthlm 39. E. läk. i Nässjö distr. 39, und :läk. v. Säters sjukh. 39-40, v. Växjö las. 40-43, v. san. i Fur samt und :läk. v. las. i Sveg 43, numera prakt. läk. i Nässjö.
translated: Håkansson, Enar A’lf, MD, Nässjö, b. April 27, 1904 in Turinge, StMms 1, to parents Oscar Ferdinand H. and Anna Maria Hallborg. Married to Margit Persson. Children: Bengt b. 1944, Hans b. 1946.  Studied for exams in Västervik in 1924, received medical degree (med. kand.) in Lund in 1933, and became a licensed physician (med. lic.) in Stockholm in 1939. Became a resident doctor in the Nässjö district in 1939, and an assistant physician at Säters Hospital from 1939-1940, followed by the Växjö Hospital from 1940-1943. In 1943, he worked as a physician at the Fur sanatorium and as an assistant physician at a hospital in Sveg. Currently he is a practicing physician in Nässjö.
